The coronavirus crisis has seen three months of tournaments cancelled already, with Wimbledon announcing last week they would be abandoning their 2020 Championships. The world tennis association (WTA) have been further hit by the Rogers Cup in August being cancelled too, with that decision being taken by the local government in Quebec. No one currently knows when the tennis schedule will be able to resume, but Halep is preparing for the worst. “For the worst-case scenario in my head is 2020 going to be cancelled,” she said. “I’m sure we are going to pass this period, if we listen and if we stay safe at home. “But for the moment the break is going to be longer and through July. My longest break was three weeks until this break. --News24--